body:
Request code 12 = [`XConfigureWindow`](https://cgit.freedesktop.org/xorg/proto/xproto/tree/Xproto.h#n2033). Since the DPR is infinite, and the window size Alacritty requests is presumably a function of that, X11 is asked to resize the window to something ridiculous, hence the ¨integer parameter out of range for operation¨. This is why I added that simplistic error logging, since as you can see, the line printed by `expect` is quite misleading; in future versions of winit I hope to automatically translate the request code to the relevant request name.

My understanding is that `device_pixel_ratio` is a function of winit's `Window::hidpi_factor`, and that Alacritty resizes the window immediately after creation in response to this info. What math goes into `device_pixel_ratio`? Either way, this is likely some issue with how winit calculates DPI wrt XRandR's supplied data. @Tristan971 what's the output of `xrandr --listmonitors --verbose`? You could also tell me the output of this little winit program:

```rust
extern crate winit;

fn main() {
    let event_loop = winit::EventsLoop::new();
    for monitor in event_loop.get_available_monitors() {
        println!("{:#?}", monitor);
    }
}
```

The info about the winit examples isn't relevant. On X11, creating a window without drawing to it just populates it with a copy of whatever's behind it at the time of creation (Windows fills it with white, but any areas exposed by resizing are black, and on macOS it's transparent... this was just some fun trivia). Besides that, the winit examples just create windows of some default 800x600 physical size, so this couldn't happen there.

Googling "xrandr 0mm x 0mm" reveals that this can happen. This also might be relevant, though I haven't dug into it much: http://xpra.org/trac/ticket/728

Anyway, the ultimate solution here is likely to just add this to the beginning of `calc_dpi_factor`:
```rust
if width_mm == 0 || height_mm == 0 {
    return 1.0;
}
```

There's not really anything else we can do, though once logging is added it would be good to emit a warning here.

@Woolworths @Tristan971 This branch might fix the issue:
https://github.com/chrisduerr/alacritty/tree/winit-xorg-bugfix

Please let me know if it works for you, if it does I'll open the PR upstream with winit.
